article.headline: Hawaii 81, Nebraska 72
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Matt Lojeski scored 17 points to lead Hawaii to an 81-72 win over Nebraska in the semifinals of the Rainbow Classic Friday night. Ahmet Gueye had 16 points and 11 rebounds for Hawaii (7-4) and Bobby Nash added 11 points. Ryan Anderson led Nebraska (7-3) with 29 points and Charles Richardson added 13. Hawaii, which scored the first eight points of the game, took an early 23-10 lead. The Rainbow Warriors led 43-23 at halftime. Nebraska used full court pressure late in the game to close to within nine, 72-63. But Hawaii made nine-of-12 free throws in the final two minutes to hold on to the victory. Nebraska coach Doc Sadler was ejected after picking up his second technical foul with 5:13 remaining in the first half. Hawaii faces Creighton for the Rainbow Classic championship Saturday night.
